{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8140beb-463e-445b-8fb0-0568c112f515","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project too:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"35e67e2a-b01c-4ac9-bcec-3bfe3e3dbdcf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":191,"requestId":"9830:3A1214:1E0352:275850:69FFDDE6"},"id":"aa40c157-f1d7-4e98-9309-ed32f88638fc","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:22:50.869Z","parentId":"5625dea9-fc3c-4793-aee3-73a4e286ae7d"}
